  "text": "Mainly DP thymocytes are subjected to thymic selection processes although superantigen-mediated deletion affects also CD4 + SP thymocytes (3). CD8 + SP thymocytes have already undergone positive selection, thereby differentiating to a stage refractory to VSV8-triggered deletion in N15 H-2 b mice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus, gene-induction common to DP and SP thymocytes can be principally viewed as related to T cell lineage activation, whereas genes preferentially expressed in SP thymocytes relate to more mature function. In contrast, genes that are exclusively induced in DP thymocytes are likely to be pivotal in selection. In order to determine which genes encode components of the DP thymocyte selection process rather than elements of a more general T-lineage-activation pathway, we compared the expression pro®le of CD4 + CD8 + DP thymocytes with that of CD8 + SP thymocytes.",
